---
// Core Pillars section - 7 operational modules
---

<section class="py-20 lg:py-32 bg-gray-50" id="pillars">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-accent mb-4">
        Seven Connected Pillars
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-extrabold text-primary mb-6">
        Every Part of Your Business,<br>Finally in One System
      </h2>
    </header>
    
    <!-- Pillars Grid -->
    <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
      <!-- CRM -->
      <article class="relative p-8 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl hover:shadow-lg hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all">
        <span class="text-xs font-bold text-accent tracking-wider mb-4 block">01</span>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">CRM & Lead Management</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">
          <strong class="text-red-600">The problem:</strong> Enquiries arrive on WhatsApp, email, website, phone. 
          They get lost, go cold, or get followed up by three different people.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
          <strong class="text-green-600">Now:</strong> Every lead in one pipeline. See who's following up. 
          Track the journey from first message to confirmed booking. 
          Never lose a ₹2 lakh trek enquiry in chat history again.
        </p>
      </article>
      
      <!-- Booking -->
      <article class="relative p-8 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl hover:shadow-lg hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all">
        <span class="text-xs font-bold text-accent tracking-wider mb-4 block">02</span>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">Booking Engine</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">
          <strong class="text-red-600">The problem:</strong> Bookings scattered across spreadsheets. 
          Payment status unclear. Guest details in different places.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
          <strong class="text-green-600">Now:</strong> One booking record, everything attached — payments, documents, 
          special requests, communication history. From draft to completed trip, 
          full visibility.
        </p>
      </article>
      
      <!-- Inventory -->
      <article class="relative p-8 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl hover:shadow-lg hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all">
        <span class="text-xs font-bold text-accent tracking-wider mb-4 block">03</span>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">Inventory & Departures</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">
          <strong class="text-red-600">The problem:</strong> "How many seats left on the Dec 15 departure?" 
          requires checking three files and calling the operations manager.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
          <strong class="text-green-600">Now:</strong> Real-time seat availability. Automatic status updates. 
          Hold management for pending payments. Overbooking prevention. 
          Waitlist automation.
        </p>
      </article>
      
      <!-- Gear - Featured -->
      <article class="relative p-8 bg-gradient-to-br from-accent/5 to-accent-light/10 border border-accent rounded-xl hover:shadow-lg hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all">
        <span class="text-xs font-bold text-accent tracking-wider mb-4 block">04</span>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">Gear Management</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">
          <strong class="text-red-600">The problem:</strong> Expensive equipment disappears after trips. 
          Damaged gear gets sent out. No one knows what's where.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">
          <strong class="text-green-600">Now:</strong> Every tent, sleeping bag, and harness tracked. 
          Assigned per trip. Condition inspected on return. 
          Maintenance scheduled. Rentals managed. No more ₹5 lakh annual gear loss.
        </p>
        <a href="#gear" class="inline-block text-sm font-semibold text-accent hover:text-accent-dark transition-colors">
          Deep dive into Gear Management →
        </a>
      </article>
      
      <!-- HRMS -->
      <article class="relative p-8 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl hover:shadow-lg hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all">
        <span class="text-xs font-bold text-accent tracking-wider mb-4 block">05</span>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">HRMS & Staff Operations</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">
          <strong class="text-red-600">The problem:</strong> "Is Rajesh available for the Annapurna trip?" 
          Who knows his leave balance? What's his pay for last month?
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
          <strong class="text-green-600">Now:</strong> Staff availability calendar. Trip assignments with acceptance. 
          Attendance from the field. Payroll with trip incentives. 
          Leave management that knows about scheduled departures.
        </p>
      </article>
      
      <!-- Vendors -->
      <article class="relative p-8 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl hover:shadow-lg hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all">
        <span class="text-xs font-bold text-accent tracking-wider mb-4 block">06</span>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">Vendor & Supplier Management</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">
          <strong class="text-red-600">The problem:</strong> Which vehicle vendor is reliable? 
          What's pending to the Lukla hotel? Cash flows out with no trail.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
          <strong class="text-green-600">Now:</strong> Vendor profiles with performance history. 
          Automated payable generation per booking. Settlement tracking. 
          Know exactly who owes what, and why.
        </p>
      </article>
      
      <!-- WhatsApp -->
      <article class="relative p-8 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl hover:shadow-lg hover:-translate-y-0.5 transition-all md:col-span-2 lg:col-span-1">
        <span class="text-xs font-bold text-accent tracking-wider mb-4 block">07</span>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-primary mb-4">WhatsApp Operations</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">
          <strong class="text-red-600">The problem:</strong> WhatsApp is where business happens — 
          but it's also where information goes to die.
        </p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
          <strong class="text-green-600">Now:</strong> WhatsApp messages linked to bookings. 
          Automated confirmations and reminders. Field staff check-ins via chat. 
          The conversation becomes part of the record.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>